      "characters-title": "Characters",
      
      "char-1-name": "The First - Created to lead us",
      "char-1-desc": "The oldest of the ragdoll creatures. He was the first to witness the war between humans and robots and sees himself as the natural leader of the nine. He is proud and arrogant, yet also very cowardly and even deceitful. Nonetheless, he ends up performing a heroic act by saving the Ninth from death. According to Glukhovsky's interpretation, the First carries the memories of the Chancellor — the one who took the Machine from the Scientist before its soul was complete and used it for evil purposes.",

      "char-2-name": "The Second - Created to give us hope",
      "char-2-desc": "A kind and optimistic little inventor who created many technical gadgets out of various scraps. He even manages to repair the Ninth and restore his ability to speak. While trying to save him, the Ninth accidentally activates the Machine. The Second’s soul is the first to be consumed by it. According to Glukhovsky's interpretation, the Second is the Scientist’s assistant and loyal companion who worked under him for decades.",
      
      "char-3,4-name": "The Third and the Fourth - Created to teach us",
      "char-3,4-desc": "The little ones, the twin brothers Third and Fourth, love to read together; their shelter is set up in an old library. They lack the gift of speech, but can communicate with each other using rapid blinking of their lamp-like eyes, and can even project slide shows. According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, they carry the memories of the professor’s twin sons — first graders, as the Ninth himself claims.",
      
      "char-5-name": "The Fifth - Created to guide us",
      "char-5-desc": "A one-eyed ragdoll who lost his left eye during the war between humans and machines. He has a gift for sewing and “heals” the Ninth by stitching his torn arm back on. Slightly timid but kind and affectionate, he quickly becomes close friends with the Ninth. According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, he was a doctor who cured the Scientist of a terrible disease and tended to wounded soldiers during the war with the machines. He once said, “I never studied this, but my hands just know what to do,” a phrase later echoed by the Ninth.",
      
      "char-6-name": "The Sixth - Created to reveal the secret to us",
      "char-6-desc": "A mad doll with quill-like fingers, constantly drawing images of the artifact. Unlike the others, he knows its nature but cannot fully remember. He has mismatched eyes. According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, the Sixth holds the memories of the unfortunate engineer who activated the Machine.",
      
      "char-7-name": "The Seventh - Created to fight for us",
      "char-7-desc": "A hunter-type character, very brave and agile. She fought and killed machine-monsters attacking the dolls. At the same time, she is sweet and caring, looking after the twin brothers Third and Fourth. She cherishes the Ninth and the twins deeply. Her feelings for the Ninth shift throughout the film but eventually grow into love. According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, she holds the memories of the Scientist’s wife — fearless and yet nurturing.",
      
      "char-8-name": "The Eighth - Created to protect us",
      "char-8-desc": "A tall and powerful ragdoll who serves as the First’s loyal bodyguard. He carries a magnet on his back to which his weapons — blades from knives and scissors — are attached. The magnet also feeds his secret addiction: the Eighth derives pleasure from magnetizing his electric brain, causing him to forget everything around him. He is recklessly brave and willing to fight even stronger foes (as shown in his battle with the bird). According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, he holds the memories of the Chancellor’s bodyguard, who remained loyal to the Chancellor until the very end.",
      
      "char-9-name": "The Ninth - Created to save us",
      "char-9-desc": "The main protagonist of the film, the last ragdoll, who remained in the laboratory and thus did not witness the war between humans and robots. It appears the Scientist rushed his creation, as the Ninth was built without a voice box. He is not the strongest or most agile, but he is the bravest of all the dolls. Though responsible for activating the Machine, he also uncovers the legacy left to him by the Scientist and ultimately makes the right decision. Upon first meeting, he falls in love with the Seventh, who eventually reciprocates his feelings. According to Glukhovsky’s interpretation, the Ninth contains the Scientist’s entire soul and all of his memories.",
      
      "char-10-scientist-name": "The Scientist - Created nine important dolls",
      "char-10-scientist-desc": "The creator of the Machine. Too late—after the Chancellor's soldiers removed him from his creation—he realized the devastating mistake he had made for all humanity. Using the artifact he created, he transferred his soul into the ragdoll creatures he had designed. The Ninth sees his mummified body on the lab floor. In Glukhovsky’s interpretation, the Scientist, fascinated by alchemy, didn’t create the artifact himself but merely used it to transfer his soul into the body of the Ninth.",
      
      "char-11-chancellor-name": "The Chancellor - Created the machine to conquer the world",
      "char-11-chancellor-desc": "A dictator who built the Machine. Using its mechanical creations, he started and won a world war — but in the end, the machines turned against humanity.",
      
      "char-12-machine-name": "The Machine - An artificial intelligence with its own plans",
      "char-12-machine-desc": "A massive robot with many claws. In reality, it’s a medium-sized sphere with two small arms. But once the Chancellor placed it in a body, it began absorbing souls and constructing killer robots. The Scientist managed to retrieve the artifact from the Machine, as it remembered him and allowed him near. Later, the Ninth uses the artifact to recover the stolen souls and destroy the artificial intelligence.",
      
      "char-13-beastcat-name": "Beast-Cat - The Machine’s last hope",
      "char-13-beastcat-desc": "It was created before the Machine came to life (it was meant to awaken it); it appeared in the short film, where it died falling from a height. In the full-length film, it was beheaded by the Seventh.",
      
      "char-14-birdbeast-name": "Bird-Beast - Hunter of the dolls",
      "char-14-birdbeast-desc": "The first creation of the Machine after being activated by the Ninth — a flying robot with a harpoon tail. It drove the dolls out of the chapel and injured the Seventh. Constructed from a mechanism stitched with flag scraps forming wings, and a rear propeller for fast flight, along with a tail-mounted harpoon. It has eight eyes and a beak made of kitchen knives. The creature was defeated when it caught its harpoon on the propeller of a crashed plane near the ruins. The Fifth and Sixth managed to start the engine, which destroyed the robot.",
      
      "char-15-seamstress-name": "The Seamstress - The second hunter, stealthy and cunning",
      "char-15-seamstress-desc": "The second creation of the Machine. A serpent with a terrifying face and the body of the Second attached to its tail, which it used to hypnotize the dolls and sew them into itself using dozens of sewing needles. It managed to capture the Eighth and the Seventh and delivered them to the Machine. The Ninth failed to save the Eighth, whose soul was consumed, but managed to rescue the Seventh by luring the Seamstress deep into the mechanisms, ultimately destroying her.",
      
