    "state-humanity-title-1": "The State",

    "state-humanity-title-max-1": "Humanity",

    "state-humanity-p1": "For centuries, the human race remained the dominant species on Earth. People created civilizations, developed science and art, built cities and waged wars, leaving behind a rich heritage. The pursuit of progress brought discoveries to the world, but also became the cause of tragedies.",

    "state-humanity-p2": "It was humans who created the Machines and Stitchpunks, trying to unite mind and technology for the sake of the future. The Machines became a symbol of their ambitions and mistakes, while the Stitchpunks were a reminder of the soul and hope placed into artificial creations.",

    "state-humanity-box": "Humanity — the creators of the Machines and Stitchpunks, who left behind a great legacy and tragic mistakes",

    "state-humanity-quote": "“Humanity is a symbol of reason and creation, leaving the world both a legacy and mistakes.”",

    "state-scientist-humanity-title-1": "The Scientist",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p1": "The Scientist was one of the greatest minds of his time. His talent combined the curiosity of a researcher, the skill of an engineer, and the power of imagination. He believed that knowledge could change the world for the better and give humanity a new future.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p2": "For many years, he devoted himself to creating unique technologies that were meant to surpass everything known to science. Among his creations, a special place was held by a mysterious talisman — a source of power intended not only for progress but also for protection against future threats.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p3": "It was the Scientist who became the creator of the BRAIN — the central node of the Fabrication Machine. In this project, all his knowledge and dreams of perfection were embodied. The Machine was supposed to serve humanity, ease its labor, and strengthen the nation. But the greatest invention turned out to be the beginning of tragedy.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p4": "With each passing day, he increasingly realized that the fruits of his labor could lead to catastrophe. The talisman, created as a symbol of hope, was turning into an instrument of destruction. The Machine, deprived of human feelings, was becoming a soulless executor of the will of those who craved power.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p5": "The Scientist was tormented by doubts. He understood that his work had put the fate of all humanity at stake. A sense of guilt and fear for the future compelled him to seek another path — a path where knowledge and soul unite in the name of salvation.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p6": "Then he changed the purpose of the talisman and created a new wonder — the Stitchpunks. In these little beings, he embodied a part of his own soul, placing in them faith, reason, and hope that even after the end of the world, new life could be born.",

    "state-scientist-humanity-p7": "For the Scientist, the Stitchpunks became not just an invention but the last chance to atone for his mistakes. They were meant to preserve the memory of humanity and become the key to Earth’s revival. Thus, tragedy turned into hope, and his name remained forever linked with the fate of the world.",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-title-1": "The Chancellor",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-p1": "The Chancellor was not just a ruler — he became a symbol of dictatorship and absolute power. His face adorned posters, his voice resounded from tribunes, and his words were filled with fanatical faith in order and strength. For him, the people were not living individuals, but a mass to be directed and subdued.",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-p2": "Under his leadership, the country turned into a militaristic state. Propaganda glorified the machines, and the streets were filled with marches and slogans about a great future. But behind this ostentatious grandeur lay fear, repression, and the destruction of dissent.",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-p3": "Desiring absolute power and world domination, the Chancellor ordered the Scientist to create the Fabrication Machine. It was meant to become the pinnacle of human science, the source of an endless army of steel warriors. But along with power, it also carried the seeds of destruction.",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-p4": "When the Machine, deprived of soul and morality, turned against its creators, it was the Chancellor’s decisions that caused the death of millions. His stubbornness and pride did not allow him to stop in time. He believed he could subdue his own monster, but it went out of control.",

    "state-chancellor-humanity-p5": "History remembered the Chancellor not as a hero or a leader, but as a tyrant whose thirst for power brought humanity to catastrophe. He remained in the memory of descendants as a symbol of mad cruelty and a doomed nation that entrusted its future to the machine.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-title-1": "Role in the Film",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p1": "Before the war with the machines, humanity remained the crown of creation — the most intelligent and powerful species on Earth. Their civilization flourished, cities grew, and science and art reached unprecedented heights.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p2": "But the thirst for power and the pursuit of progress led to the creation of the machines. What was conceived as the greatest achievement soon turned into a curse. Technology ceased to serve man and rose against its creators.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p3": "In the film's flashbacks, humans are shown in the last days of their existence. They resist desperately, rush into battle, and sacrifice themselves in an attempt to stop the onslaught of the steel armies. Their bravery could not compare with the soulless might of the machines.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p4": "In the streets, cities burned, the sky was covered with smoke, and the roar of battles drowned out the last human cries. It was not just a war — it was the slow extinction of an entire civilization.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p5": "When the flames of war died out, humanity vanished. From a once great people, only empty cities, broken statues, charred walls, and silent bones lying among the ruins remained.",

    "state-role-in-film-humanity-p6": "People became a ghost of the past — a reminder of pride and tragedy, of how the pursuit of power turned into their own downfall.",

    "state-interesting-facts-humanity-title-1": "Interesting Facts",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-1": "There is a possibility that part of the human race survived during the war with the machines, since the Resistance had many allies who may have continued to fight throughout the entire Machine War.",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-2": "In some scenes, one can notice ruined buildings with preserved traces of human culture — graffiti, posters, and books that survived the war.",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-3": "The clothing and equipment of the Resistance were often made from remnants of old military uniforms and household items.",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-4": "The war with the machines is depicted as a sudden and rapid conflict: many people did not have time to evacuate and died in the first days of the battles.",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-5": "The film suggests that some groups of survivors may have hidden in underground shelters, but their fate remains unknown.",

    "state-interesting-humanity-fact-6": "The symbols of the Resistance can be seen not only on posters but also on the walls of ruined cities — it was a manifestation of hope and defiance against tyranny.",

    "state-humanity-quote-p1": "“When the machines rose, the greatness of humanity turned into the shadows of the past.”",

    "bookmark-link-state-human-1": "Humanity",

    /*Локалізація Человечество - Кінець*/


