    "menu-creators-developer": "Creators and Developer",

    "creators-dev-title-1": "Creators and Developer",

    "creators-dev-creators-of-cartoon-1": "Creators of the Cartoon",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-title-1": "SHANE RICHARD ACKER — CREATOR OF THE WORLD OF “9”",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-desc-1": "<b>Shane Richard Acker</b> is an American director, screenwriter, and animator, born in 1971 in Illinois (USA). He studied architecture, but his imagination and desire to create worlds led him beyond blueprints — into the world of animation.",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-desc-2": "His short film <b>“9”</b> (2005) became his graduation project, which received worldwide acclaim and an <b>“Academy Award”</b> nomination. This story about small ragdoll creatures carrying fragments of the human soul impressed audiences so deeply that a full-length feature film was soon made based on it, becoming a unique example of dark philosophical animation.",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-desc-3": "Inspired by the themes of loss, hope, and human essence, Acker created a world where technology and soul intertwine, and the visual style combines architectural precision with emotional depth. His approach to animation became a reflection of the idea that even in artificial creations one can find an echo of humanity.",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-caption-1": "Director and animator of the film “9” (2009)<br>Creator of the original short film project “9” (2005)",

    "creators-dev-shane-richard-acker-quote-1": "“I wanted to show that even in a lifeless world, the spark of a soul can rekindle hope.”",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-title-1": "TIM BURTON — MAIN PRODUCER OF THE FILM “9”",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-desc-1": "<b>Tim Burton</b> (Timothy Walter Burton) — an American director, producer, screenwriter, artist, and author, born on <b>August 25, 1958</b> in Burbank, California (USA). He is known for his dark, gothic, and visually expressive films that intertwine fantasy, irony, and philosophical depth.",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-desc-2": "He received his education at the <b>California Institute of the Arts</b>, where he developed his unique visual style inspired by animation and artistic illustration. Early in his career, he worked at <b>Walt Disney</b> studios, but soon began creating his own projects, becoming a cult figure in cinema.",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-desc-3": "In the film <b>“9” (2009)</b>, Tim Burton acted as the <b>main producer</b>, supporting director Shane Richard Acker and helping to bring his short film project to the big screen. Thanks to his involvement, the movie gained wide recognition and became part of the dark aesthetic characteristic of Burton’s works.",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-caption-1": "Main producer of the film “9” (2009)<br>Known for films such as “Edward Scissorhands”, “Beetlejuice”, “Sleepy Hollow”, “Corpse Bride”",

    "creators-dev-tim-burton-quote-1": "“I have always sought to combine darkness with beauty, to show that even in gloom there is life and poetry.”",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-title-1": "PAMELA PETTLER — SCREENWRITER OF THE FILM “9”",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-desc-1": "<b>Pamela Pettler</b> (Pamela Pettler) is an American screenwriter known for her work in animation and dark fantasy. Her style combines gloomy fairy-tale elements, dark humor, and warm human themes.",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-desc-2": "Before the film <b>“9”</b>, Pamela wrote screenplays for <b>“Corpse Bride”</b> (2005) and <b>“Monster House”</b> (2006), where she demonstrated her ability to blend gothic style, irony, and character-driven drama.",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-desc-3": "In <b>“9” (2009)</b>, she adapted Shane Acker’s short film into a complete screenplay, strengthening the philosophical and emotional focus of the story. Her work added depth to the film and made the narrative cohesive and heartfelt.",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-desc-4": "Thanks to her attention to detail, the story about mechanical beings became a touching parable about humanity and hope in a soulless world.",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-caption-1": "Screenwriter of the film “9” (2009)<br>Also: “Corpse Bride” (2005), “Monster House” (2006)",

    "creators-dev-pamela-pettler-quote-1": "“A story must breathe — even when the world around is silent.”",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-title-1": "DEBORAH LURIE — COMPOSER OF THE FILM “9”",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-desc-1": "<b>Deborah Lurie</b> (Deborah Lurie) is an American composer, arranger, and music producer known for her work in film and television. Her style blends emotional orchestration with modern elements, creating powerful and atmospheric soundscapes.",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-desc-2": "Before working on <b>“9”</b>, Lurie contributed to the music of projects such as <b>“Monster House”</b> (2006) and <b>“The Spiderwick Chronicles”</b> (2008), where she demonstrated her ability to convey dynamics and depth through music.",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-desc-3": "In <b>“9” (2009)</b>, she composed a soundtrack that emphasizes the film’s philosophical and emotional atmosphere. Lurie’s music enhances the themes of hope, sacrifice, and rebirth, making each moment more profound and cinematic.",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-desc-4": "Her melodies connected the cold mechanical world with human emotions, turning sound into the voice of the soul — quiet yet powerful.",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-caption-1": "Composer of the film “9” (2009)<br>Also: “Monster House” (2006), “The Spiderwick Chronicles” (2008)",

    "creators-dev-deborah-lurie-quote-1": "“Music should not only sound — it should feel.”",

    "creators-dev-studios-title-1": "STUDIOS — FOCUS FEATURES / RELATIVITY MEDIA",

    "creators-dev-studios-desc-1": "<b>Focus Features</b> and <b>Relativity Media</b> became the main studios that supported the production of the feature film <b>“9” (2009)</b>. Their collaboration provided the project with not only financial but also creative stability, allowing an independent idea to achieve a large-scale realization.",

    "creators-dev-studios-desc-2": "<b>Focus Features</b> is known for its dedication to auteur cinema and original animated projects that value not only visual effects but also profound themes. Under its banner, such films as <b>“Coraline”</b> (2009) and <b>“Kubo and the Two Strings”</b> (2016) were released.",

    "creators-dev-studios-desc-3": "<b>Relativity Media</b> made a key contribution to the organization of production and the distribution of the film, uniting the efforts of talented creators with the technical capabilities of major studios.",

    "creators-dev-studios-desc-4": "Thanks to this collaboration, <b>“9”</b> became an example of how an independent idea can resonate on the scale of major cinema while preserving its soul and originality.",

    "creators-dev-studios-caption-1": "Studios that produced the film “9” (2009)<br>Known for projects such as “Coraline” (2009) and “Kubo and the Two Strings”(2016)",

    "creators-dev-studios-quote-1": "“Even the boldest idea needs those who help it sound louder.”",
    
    "creators-dev-developer-title-1": "Project Developer",

    "creators-dev-developer-subtitle-1": "Vitaly Kosenko — author and developer of the website",

